Ok, voici un bloc de conf “bref” à coller (AKS / shuffle / fetchfailed).
Il y a 2 versions selon si tu peux monter un volume local.
✅ Version recommandée (avec volume local)
YAML
Copier le code
sparkConf:
  spark.local.dir: "/var/data/spark"

  spark.sql.shuffle.partitions: "200"
  spark.sql.adaptive.enabled: "true"
  spark.sql.adaptive.coalescePartitions.enabled: "true"
  spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled: "true"
  spark.sql.files.maxRecordsPerFile: "500000"

  spark.kubernetes.executor.request.cores: "2"
  spark.kubernetes.executor.limit.cores: "2"

  spark.task.maxFailures: "8"
  spark.stage.maxConsecutiveAttempts: "8"
  spark.shuffle.io.maxRetries: "20"
  spark.shuffle.io.retryWait: "10s"
  spark.network.timeout: "800s"
  spark.executor.heartbeatInterval: "60s"
Et à ajouter (SparkApplication) :
YAML
Copier le code
spec:
  executor:
    volumeMounts:
      - name: spark-local-dir
        mountPath: /var/data/spark
    volumes:
      - name: spark-local-dir
        emptyDir:
          sizeLimit: 100Gi
✅ Version “sans volume” (plan B)
YAML
Copier le code
sparkConf:
  spark.sql.shuffle.partitions: "200"
  spark.sql.adaptive.enabled: "true"
  spark.sql.files.maxRecordsPerFile: "500000"

  spark.executor.instances: "10"
  spark.kubernetes.executor.request.cores: "2"
  spark.kubernetes.executor.limit.cores: "2"

  spark.task.maxFailures: "8"
  spark.stage.maxConsecutiveAttempts: "8"
  spark.shuffle.io.maxRetries: "20"
  spark.shuffle.io.retryWait: "10s"
  spark.network.timeout: "800s"
  spark.executor.heartbeatInterval: "60s"
Si tu dois choisir 1 seul truc : request.cores = 2 + limit.cores = 2 (sinon k8s te sur-pack et tu retombes en FetchFailed).
